## Built-in Codex slash commands vs Writ

Codex built-ins include `/plan`, `/review`, `/status`, `/init`, `/agent`, `/fork`, `/side`, and more ([official list](https://developers.openai.com/codex/cli/slash-commands)). Writ keeps its own `/plan`-style command files under `.codex/commands/` and does **not** rename them. Bare `/status` or `/review` in the Codex UI runs Codex's built-in. To execute **Writ's** `/status` or `/review` workflows, ask explicitly to load and follow the Markdown in `.codex/commands/status.md` or `.codex/commands/review.md`.




## Catalog source

Command and agent metadata also lives in `.writ/manifest.yaml` (upstream Writ repo). Regenerate root `SKILL.md` with `scripts/gen-skill.sh` when extending the manifest.
